Type Parameters:
T - The type of the object that refines the expandable's behaviour
S - The type of the supported expansions' marker

R - The type of the result
A - The type of the accumulator
Direct Known Subclasses:
ExpFunction, ExpPredicate
public abstract class AccumulatorExpandable<T,​S,​U extends Expansion<T,​S>,​V,​R,​A>
extends SimpleExpandable<T,​S,​U>
Represents a complex expandable that makes use of an accumulator and of inputs to manifest his behaviour based on expansions. It also produces a concrete result through the accumulator.
